==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Italian, a diminutive of [[fianca]] ‘flank’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /fɪən'ʧɛtəʊ/, /fɪən'kɛtəʊ/

===Noun===
# {{cattag|Chess}} the development of a [[bishop]] by moving it one square to a long diagonal; specifically, a set of opening moves where a [[bishop]] is [[develop]]ed to the second [[rank]] of the [[adjacent]] [[knight]] [[file]]
#:*'''1994''': I’m not a hero, I’m not even a chessboard knight.  Trying to be a priest was something of a '''fianchetto''' wasn’t it?  Clever move by a poor player. — Jeanette Winterson, ''Art & Lies''